cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper deals with dense prediction tasks in computer vision, specifically addressing the issue of boundary artifacts in decoder convolutions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel network layer and learning procedure, which involves learning task-specific feature representations, indicating a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also fit into categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves sparse convolutions in high-dimensional space, which could potentially fall under the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
